00:29:06.372 --> 00:29:10.052
foster DNA replication to move past a truncation mutation,

490
00:29:10.912 --> 00:29:14.692
haven't been tried here, but I think could be of real interest as

491
00:29:14.732 --> 00:29:14.932
well.

492
00:29:16.492 --> 00:29:17.052
So hi.

493
00:29:17.242 --> 00:29:17.492
Yeah, hi.

494
00:29:17.502 --> 00:29:20.712
Hi. Pier Paolo Claudio. I have a question regarding the

495
00:29:21.292 --> 00:29:22.262
replication of

496
00:29:23.332 --> 00:29:26.852
NPL2. So CDK9 actually phosphorylates PL2.

497
00:29:26.912 --> 00:29:30.552
Have you investigated the role of CDK9 in this?

498
00:29:30.672 --> 00:29:32.652
And also, have you investigated

499
00:29:33.532 --> 00:29:37.452
retinoblastoma? Because it's not just p53, but any, because it's

